# Ingestion & Data Handling Actions

Ingest logs (syslog, agents, APIs, cloud services)
Normalize events into a common schema
Deduplicate events
Tag events (e.g. vpn, admin_activity)
Archive old data (cold storage)

# Detection & Analytics Actions

Correlation across multiple events
Anomaly detection (baseline deviation)
Sequence detection (kill chain patterns)
Threat intel matching (IOCs)
Risk scoring (user or asset risk)

# Alert & Incident Actions

Create alerts
Suppress alerts (noise reduction)
Deduplicate alerts
Escalate alerts
Auto-close alerts
Group alerts into incidents
Change alert status (open, acknowledged, closed)
Assign alerts/incidents to analysts

# Investigation & Hunting Actions

Timeline reconstruction
Link related events
Threat hunting queries
Add analyst notes
Attach evidence

# Response & Automation (SOAR-like Actions)

Trigger playbooks
Send notifications (email, Slack, PagerDuty)
Disable user accounts
Reset passwords

# User & Access Management Actions

Create / deactivate users
Assign roles
Review permissions
Session tracking
Enforce MFA policies
Audit analyst actions

# Configuration & Admin Actions

Manage assets
Enable/disable log sources
Create/edit rules
Tune detection thresholds
Manage data retention
Health checks

# Performance & Scaling Actions

Hot vs cold storage
Rate limiting ingestion
Drop low-value logs